<dl id="un1013bl"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013bl"> (NLI.3) 13(bl)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> heart, gold <font color="green">[sketch of symbol]</font> <font color="green">[subdi]</font> 12,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The fourth centre, at <mark>the heart, is of a glowing golden colour</mark>, and each of its quadrants is divided into three parts, which gives it <mark>twelve undulations</mark>. <small> <a name="THmay1910" href="/udra/udex.htm#thmay1910"><cite title="source">The Theosophist</cite></a> (May 1910), C.W. Leadbeater, &ldquo;FORCE-CENTRES AND THE SERPENT-FIRE&rdquo; p. 1078</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07260a" href="../../../f/ff/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07260a">VI.C.07:260(a)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
